      "side": 1,
      "message": "ideally database does filtering for us, so we don\u0027t fetch what would ignore, but I understand that manually composing SQL queries makes it complex. I\u0027ve found https://github.com/Masterminds/squirrel which seems to solve this problem:\n\n  q :\u003d sq.\n    Select(\"racks.name\", \"racks.description\", \"datacenters.name\").\n    From(\"racks\").\n    Join(\"datacenters ON racks.datacenter_id \u003d datacenters.id\")\n  if len(names) \u003e 0 {\n    q \u003d q.Where(sq.Eq{\"racks.name\": names)) // no need for stringset anymore\n  }  \n  if len(datacenters) \u003e 0 {\n    q \u003d q.Where(sq.Eq{\"datacenter.name\": datacenters))\n  }  \n\neven without dynamic SQL generation, one may argue that this is more type safe because it calls Go functions for SQL operators.\n\nWith a query that does not require client-side filtering, we can further reduce duplication between L79-L98 and L114-134:\n\nfunc selectTo(c context.Context, q string, slicePtr interface{}) error {\n\tdb :\u003d database.Get(c)\nq\tif err !\u003d nil {\n\t\treturn nil, errors.Annotate(err, \"failed to get database\").Err()\n\t}\n\tdefer rows.Close()\n\n\tslicePtrV :\u003d reflect.ValueOf(slicePtr)\n\tstructType :\u003d slicePtrV.Type().Elem().Elem().Elem()\n\n\tfor rows.Next() {\n\t\trow :\u003d reflect.New(structType)\n                // here I use https://github.com/jmoiron/sqlx\n                // which seems to be useful\n\t\tif err \u003d rows.StructScan(row.Interface()); err !\u003d nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, errors.Annotate(err, \"failed to scan a row\").Err()\n\t\t}\n\t\tslicePtrV.Set(reflect.Append(slicePtrV.Elem(), row))\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\nfunc (*CrimsonService) getRacks(c context.Context, names, datacenters stringset.Set) ([]*crimson.Rack, error) {\n  q :\u003d sq....\n  var racks []*crimson.Rack\n  err :\u003d selectTo(c, q.ToSql(), \u0026racks)\n  return racks, err\n}",
      "revId": "4ea52789888975cbe249f5e94d578557a3d0dccf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
